<p>Thus far in my life, my chicken scratch handwriting has defied all attempts at optical character recognition. This is one case where artificial intelligence comes to the rescue. In this video, I demonstrate how to build a custom AI engine using Claude (it would work with any major LLM) as a machine for converting my handwritten daily logs into text for importing into Day One.… This is a post for the MacSparky Labs Pathfinder and Insider members. <a href="https://www.macsparky.com/join/">Care to join?</a> If you’re already a member,<a href="https://www.macsparky.com/?memberful_endpoint=auth"> you can log in here.</a></p>
